Placeholder so git tracks this directory and it exists on disk before
OrangeFox_A14.sh's packaging step runs.

Run 26's diagnostic dump confirmed out/target/product/kansas/root/system
is a genuinely empty real directory - nothing (no PRODUCT_PACKAGES
binaries, no AOSP-generated content) populates it under the
'adbd vendorbootimage' build goal. recovery/root/etc is an *absolute*
symlink (-> /system/etc, created by init.environ.rc's post-install
step) - correct for how the phone resolves it at real boot time, but
build-time scripts that write through it are actually targeting the CI
runner's own real "/system/etc", which doesn't exist, so those writes
silently fail. The fatal failure specifically targets
recovery/root/system/etc/recovery.fstab directly (bypassing that
symlink entirely), which needs recovery/root/system/etc/ to be a real,
existing directory - this file's only job is making that true, via the
"cp -rf device/motorola/kansas/recovery/root .../recovery/" step that
merges this device tree's own recovery/root into the build output.
